  "html": "<article class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto\">\n\n  <!-- HERO INTRO -->\n  <section class=\"gradient-flame-sunglow text-white p-5 md:p-10 rounded-2xl mb-8\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold mb-4 text-white\">When the Lights Go Out in Cuba, You Need More Than Candles</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed opacity-95\">\n      Look, if you've got family dealing with 8-hour blackouts in Havanaâ€”or worse, 12+ hours in the provincesâ€”you already know a cheap flashlight isn't cutting it anymore. Solar generators have become the lifeline. The question isn't <em>if</em> you should send one, it's which brand actually survives Cuban humidity, voltage quirks, and the inevitable \"my neighbor borrowed it for three days\" situation. Jackery and Bluetti dominate this space, but they're not interchangeable. Let me break down what actually matters when you're spending $$$$$ on something that needs to work 4,000 miles away.\n    </p>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- CONTEXT SECTION -->\n  <section class=\"prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none mb-10\">\n    <p>\n      Here's the thing about solar generators for Cuba: you're not buying for camping trips or tailgates. You're buying for survival. That means the specs that matter are completely different. <strong>LiFePO4 batteries</strong> are non-negotiableâ€”they handle heat better and last 3,000+ cycles versus maybe 500 for regular lithium-ion. Both Jackery and Bluetti have embraced this, but their approaches to wattage, charging speed, and build quality diverge in ways that matter.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      The other reality? Shipping costs. A 50-pound unit might be technically superior, but if it costs $200 to ship and gets flagged at customs for being \"too heavy for personal use,\" what's the point? I've seen families burned by this. Weight-to-capacity ratio is your friend here.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      And voltageâ€”Cuba runs on 110V/220V depending on the neighborhood and the wiring situation (which, let's be honest, can be creative). Every unit here handles both, but some do it more gracefully than others.\n    </p>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- QUICK ANSWER BOX -->\n  <section class=\"bg-sunglow/10 border-2 border-sunglow p-5 md:p-8 rounded-xl my-8\">\n    <h3 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-raisin dark:text-white mb-3\">The Quick Answer</h3>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 text-base md:text-lg mb-4\">\n      For most Cuban families, the <strong>Bluetti AC180</strong> hits the sweet spot: 1152Wh capacity, insanely fast charging (0-80% in 45 minutes before you ship it), and enough output to run a fridge, fans, and charge phones simultaneously. It's lighter than the Jackery 2000 v2 and more powerful than the Jackery 1000 v2. If budget allows and you need serious capacity, the Jackery Explorer 2000 v2 is the tankâ€”but it's heavier and pricier.\n    </p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0C1SMJTDT?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors\">\n      See the Bluetti AC180 â†’\n    </a>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- STAT CALLOUT -->\n  <div class=\"text-center my-10\">\n    <span class=\"text-5xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold text-flame\">2,700W</span>\n    <p class=\"text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2\">Peak surge power on the Bluetti AC180â€”enough to start a small fridge compressor</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- FEATURED PRODUCT - TOP PICK -->\n  <section class=\"mb-10\">\n    <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl ring-2 ring-lime ring-offset-2 ring-offset-white dark:ring-offset-slate-900\">\n      <span class=\"bg-lime text-raisin px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-4 inline-block\">Editor's Pick for Cuba</span>\n      <div class=\"flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6\">\n        <div class=\"w-full md:w-64 shrink-0\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71Lg8i251IL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Bluetti AC180 Portable Power Station - Best solar generator for Cuban blackouts\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-xl w-full h-64 object-contain bg-slate-50\">\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n          <h3 data-asin=\"B0C1SMJTDT\" class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">Bluetti AC180</h3>\n          <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-3\">\n            <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.6â˜…</span>\n            <span class=\"text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">465 reviews</span>\n            <span class=\"text-flame font-semibold\">$$$$$</span>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4\">\n            1152Wh capacity with LiFePO4 chemistry that'll last 3,000+ charge cycles. The 1800W continuous (2700W surge) handles fridges, fans, and medical equipment without blinking. What sells it for Cuba? That 45-minute charge to 80%â€”you can top it off during the 4 hours of power they get.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4\">\n            <strong>VERDICT:</strong> The Goldilocks unitâ€”not too heavy to ship, not too weak to matter. This is what I'd send my own family.\n          </p>\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0C1SMJTDT?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors\">\n            Check Price on Amazon â†’\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- PULL QUOTE -->\n  <blockquote class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl italic text-flame border-l-4 border-flame pl-6 my-10\">\n    \"The best generator is the one that's charged when the lights go outâ€”not the one with the biggest specs.\"\n  </blockquote>\n\n  <!-- ASYMMETRIC GRID - POWER OPTIONS -->\n  <section class=\"my-10\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6\">When You Need Serious Power</h2>\n    \n    <div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6\">\n      <!-- FEATURED LARGE CARD -->\n      <div class=\"md:col-span-2 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg ring-2 ring-sunglow ring-offset-2 ring-offset-white dark:ring-offset-slate-900\">\n        <span class=\"bg-sunglow text-raisin px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-4 inline-block\">Maximum Capacity</span>\n        <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5\">\n          <div class=\"w-full sm:w-48 md:w-56 shrink-0\">\n            <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61BnZCjgnQL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Jackery Explorer 2000 v2 - High capacity solar generator for extended blackouts\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-56 object-contain bg-slate-50\">\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n            <h3 data-asin=\"B0DFG2WDQH\" class=\"text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">Jackery Explorer 2000 v2</h3>\n            <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-3\">\n              <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.7â˜…</span>\n              <span class=\"text-flame font-semibold\">$$$$$</span>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-3\">\n              2042Wh of LiFePO4 goodness. This is the \"run the whole house\" optionâ€”fridge, TV, multiple fans, charge everything. The 2200W output handles pretty much any appliance except AC units. Downside? It's heavy. Shipping this beast will cost you, and customs might raise an eyebrow.\n            </p>\n            <p class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3\">\n              <strong>VERDICT:</strong> For large families or homes with medical equipment that can't go without power. Worth the shipping headache.\n            </p>\n            <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DFG2WDQH?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-5 py-2 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors text-sm\">\n              View on Amazon â†’\n            </a>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      \n      <!-- SMALLER SIDE CARD -->\n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61JVKysP1nL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Jackery Explorer 1000 v2 - Mid-range solar generator\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-48 object-contain bg-slate-50 mb-4\">\n        <h3 data-asin=\"B0D7PPG25F\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">Jackery Explorer 1000 v2</h3>\n        <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-3\">\n          <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.7â˜…</span>\n          <span class=\"text-flame font-semibold\">$$$$$</span>\n        </div>\n        <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm mb-3\">\n          1070Wh, 1500W output. The \"I trust Jackery\" option. Solid build, reliable brand, but the AC180 beats it on specs for similar money. Stillâ€”Jackery's customer service is legendary if something goes wrong.\n        </p>\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0D7PPG25F?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-slate-300 dark:hover:bg-slate-600 transition-colors text-sm\">\n          Check Price â†’\n        </a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- HEAD TO HEAD COMPARISON -->\n  <section class=\"my-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6\">Head-to-Head: Mid-Range Showdown</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">The ~1000Wh category is where most families should look. Here's how they stack up:</p>\n    \n    <div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 md:gap-6\">\n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <div class=\"flex items-center gap-3 mb-4\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71Lg8i251IL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Bluetti AC180\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"w-16 h-16 object-contain rounded-lg bg-slate-50\">\n          <div>\n            <h3 class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white\">Bluetti AC180</h3>\n            <span class=\"text-sm text-lime font-semibold\">WINNER</span>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <ul class=\"space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">\n          <li class=\"flex items-start gap-2\"><span class=\"text-lime font-bold\">âœ“</span> 1152Wh capacity</li>\n          <li class=\"flex items-start gap-2\"><span class=\"text-lime font-bold\">âœ“</span> 1800W / 2700W surge</li>\n          <li class=\"flex items-start gap-2\"><span class=\"text-lime font-bold\">âœ“</span> 45-min to 80% charge</li>\n          <li class=\"flex items-start gap-2\"><span class=\"text-lime font-bold\">âœ“</span> 2 AC outlets</li>\n          <li class=\"flex items-start gap-2\"><span class=\"text-slate-400\">~</span> ~27 lbs</li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <div class=\"flex items-center gap-3 mb-4\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/61JVKysP1nL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Jackery 1000 v2\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"w-16 h-16 object-contain rounded-lg bg-slate-50\">\n          <div>\n            <h3 class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white\">Jackery 1000 v2</h3>\n            <span class=\"text-sm text-slate-500\">Runner-up</span>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <ul class=\"space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">\n          <li class=\"flex items-start gap-2\"><span class=\"text-slate-400\">~</span> 1070Wh capacity</li>\n          <li class=\"flex items-start gap-2\"><span class=\"text-red-500 font-bold\">âœ—</span> 1500W output (lower)</li>\n          <li class=\"flex items-start gap-2\"><span class=\"text-lime font-bold\">âœ“</span> 1-hour full charge</li>\n          <li class=\"flex items-start gap-2\"><span class=\"text-slate-400\">~</span> Multiple outlets</li>\n          <li class=\"flex items-start gap-2\"><span class=\"text-lime font-bold\">âœ“</span> Lighter build</li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- PRODUCT COMPARISON TOOL -->\n  <section class=\"my-10\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4\">Compare All Options Side-by-Side</h2>\n    <product-comparison products=\"B0C1SMJTDT,B0D7PPG25F,B0DFG2WDQH,B0F42CSQWG\" highlightBest=\"true\" />\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- COMPACT LIST - BUDGET & SPECIALIZED OPTIONS -->\n  <section class=\"my-10\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6\">Other Options Worth Knowing</h2>\n    \n    <div class=\"space-y-4\">\n      <!-- Compact Card 1 -->\n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-4 md:p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4\">\n          <div class=\"w-full sm:w-36 md:w-44 shrink-0\">\n            <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71t2GNcQZ1L._AC_SR160,134_CB1169409_QL70_.jpg\" alt=\"Bluetti Elite 100 V2 - Compact powerful generator\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-36 sm:h-40 object-contain bg-slate-50\">\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n            <h3 data-asin=\"B0F42CSQWG\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1\">Bluetti Elite 100 V2 (2025 Model)</h3>\n            <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-2\">\n              <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.5â˜…</span>\n              <span class=\"bg-royal/20 text-royal dark:text-blue-400 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">NEW</span>\n              <span class=\"text-flame font-semibold text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm mb-2\">\n              Brand new for 2025â€”35% smaller than previous gen with 4 AC outlets and 3600W surge. The 1024Wh capacity competes directly with the AC180. Too new to have reviews, but Bluetti's track record is solid. Worth watching.\n            </p>\n            <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0F42CSQWG?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-flame hover:text-flame/80 font-semibold text-sm no-underline\">View on Amazon â†’</a>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      \n      <!-- Compact Card 2 -->\n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-4 md:p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4\">\n          <div class=\"w-full sm:w-36 md:w-44 shrink-0\">\n            <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/718bZu03HCL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Bluetti AC50B - Budget-friendly option\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-36 sm:h-40 object-contain bg-slate-50\">\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n            <h3 data-asin=\"B0CZ6P84WH\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1\">Bluetti AC50B</h3>\n            <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-2\">\n              <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.6â˜…</span>\n              <span class=\"bg-sunglow/20 text-sunglow px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">Lighter Option</span>\n              <span class=\"text-flame font-semibold text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm mb-2\">\n              448Wh is smaller, but the \"Power Lifting\" feature boosts output to 1000W for short bursts. Perfect for apartments or as a secondary unit. Charges to 80% in 45 minutes. Way easier to ship than the big boys.\n            </p>\n            <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CZ6P84WH?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-flame hover:text-flame/80 font-semibold text-sm no-underline\">View on Amazon â†’</a>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      \n      <!-- Compact Card 3 -->\n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-4 md:p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4\">\n          <div class=\"w-full sm:w-36 md:w-44 shrink-0\">\n            <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81Fq5thlrnS._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Jackery Explorer 300 - Entry-level portable power\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-36 sm:h-40 object-contain bg-slate-50\">\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n            <h3 data-asin=\"B082TMBYR6\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1\">Jackery Explorer 300</h3>\n            <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-2\">\n              <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.6â˜…</span>\n              <span class=\"text-flame font-semibold text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm mb-2\">\n              Real talk: 293Wh won't run a fridge. But for phones, lights, a small fan, and a laptop? It's enough. Uses older lithium battery tech (not LiFePO4), so fewer cycles. I'd only recommend this as a supplement to a bigger unit, not the main solution.\n            </p>\n            <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B082TMBYR6?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-flame hover:text-flame/80 font-semibold text-sm no-underline\">View on Amazon â†’</a>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- SOLAR SIZING CALCULATOR -->\n  <section class=\"my-10\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4\">Calculate What Your Family Actually Needs</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-4\">Input your family's typical blackout duration and see which unit makes sense:</p>\n    <solar-sizing products=\"B0C1SMJTDT,B0DFG2WDQH,B0D7PPG25F\" blackoutHours=\"8\" location=\"urban\" />\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- SHIPPING CALCULATOR -->\n  <section class=\"my-10\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4\">Estimate Your Shipping Costs</h2>\n    <shipping-calculator products=\"B0C1SMJTDT,B0D7PPG25F,B0DFG2WDQH,B0CZ6P84WH\" destination=\"all\" />\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- CUBA-SPECIFIC CALLOUT -->\n  <section class=\"bg-royal/10 border-l-4 border-royal p-5 md:p-6 rounded-r-xl my-10\">\n    <h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-royal dark:text-blue-400 mb-3\">ðŸ‡¨ðŸ‡º Cuba-Specific Considerations</h3>\n    <ul class=\"space-y-2 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">\n      <li><strong>Humidity & salt air:</strong> LiFePO4 batteries handle heat better than lithium-ion. Both brands seal their units well, but store it away from windows near the coast.</li>\n      <li><strong>Voltage:</strong> All units here output standard 110V ACâ€”perfect for Cuba. Some also support 220V devices via adapters.</li>\n      <li><strong>Charging during apagones:</strong> Fast-charge capability matters. When power comes on for 4 hours, you need to top off fast. The AC180's 45-minute charge wins here.</li>\n      <li><strong>Weight limits:</strong> Many shipping services cap packages at 50 lbs. The Jackery 2000 v2 pushes that limitâ€”factor in packaging weight.</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- BOTTOM LINE -->\n  <section class=\"bg-raisin text-white p-5 md:p-8 rounded-2xl mt-10 not-prose\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4\">The Bottom Line</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-200 mb-4 leading-relaxed\">\n      For most families in Cuba, the <span class=\"text-sunglow font-semibold\">Bluetti AC180</span> is the smartest buy. It beats the Jackery 1000 v2 on capacity and output while being easier to ship than the Jackery 2000 v2. That 45-minute fast charge is a game-changer when power windows are unpredictable. If you need maximum capacity and can handle the shipping logistics, the Jackery 2000 v2 is the tank that'll run everythingâ€”but for most situations, the AC180 is the move.\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-300 text-sm mb-6\">\n      Whichever you choose, you're giving your family something more valuable than electronicsâ€”you're giving them peace of mind when the grid fails. Again.\n    </p>\n    <div class=\"flex flex-wrap gap-3\">\n      <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0C1SMJTDT?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-sunglow text-raisin font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-sunglow/90 transition-colors\">\n        Get the Bluetti AC180 â†’\n      </a>\n      <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DFG2WDQH?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-white/20 text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-white/30 transition-colors\">\n        Or the Jackery 2000 v2 â†’\n      </a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- CHECKLIST -->\n  <section class=\"my-10\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4\">Your Pre-Ship Checklist</h2>\n    <checklist-builder category=\"solar\" />\n  </section>\n\n</article>",
